    "short_description": {
        "value": "RS-vHeat is a multi-modal remote sensing foundation model inspired by heat conduction, supporting optical and SAR data. It uses a heat conduction operator for efficient global feature modeling, frequency domain hierarchical masking, and multi-domain reconstruction for self-supervised pretraining. RS-vHeat achieves state-of-the-art performance and efficiency across semantic segmentation, object detection, classification, and change detection tasks on 10 datasets.",
